==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Water gauge
<hw>Wa"ter gauge`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <altsp>[Written also <asp>water
gage</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A wall or bank to hold water back.</def>
<rj><au>Craig.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An instrument for measuring or ascertaining the
depth or quantity of water, or for indicating the height of its surface,
as in the boiler of a steam engine. See <er>Gauge</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Water gavel</ent>⟦br⟧
